        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>According to the 2016 Census, Hamptons had a population of 7,810. It has a sizeable immigrant population - 53% of residents have an immigrant background and 60% of individuals speak English most often at home. The median total household income in 2015 was $146,669. The golf community has a slightly higher proportion of two-person and four-person households compared to one-, two- or five or more person households. Population projections do not predict an increase in the community's population.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Hamptons has townhouses and villas. Some are opulent bungalow-style residences with attached garages. Residences offer views of fairways. Luxury homes here are golf course backing, with lush landscaping and run upwards of a million dollars.</p>
            <p>Lots sizes are typically around 0.15 of an acre. Only about 2.3% of homes are rented, the rest are occupied private dwellings.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Developer/Builder History </h3>
            <p>Tirion Properties developed Hamptons in the 1990s. The other builder in the community is Shane Homes. You can have your home custom designed by the builder. Most lots back onto greenspaces, and can accommodate a triple car garage.</p>
        </div>
