        <h2>FAQs about Hamptons Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Will I have to pay an HOA fee?</h3>
                <p>Anyone that owns a property in the Hamptons is a member of the Hamptons Homeowners Association (HHOA), a non-profit organisation that manages the assets owned by the Association. The annual homeowner's fee helps maintain and beautify neighbourhood resources such as flower beds, playgrounds, tennis courts, ball diamonds, hockey rinks and bike pathways.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What is the best place to go shopping?</h3>
                <p>The community shopping plaza has a Calgary Co-op grocery store, car wash, dry cleaner and other services. Beacon Hill shopping district is minutes away. Hamptons is bound to the north by Stoney Trail, offering quick access to Trans Canada Highway and Deerfoot Trail for more shopping.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What amenities are there nearby?</h3>
                <p>The community meets your golfing, shopping and recreation needs adequately. You can also walk down to any of the parks in the vicinity for a stroll or take your kids to play at the playgrounds. Within Hamptons, you'll always have the privilege of strolling along the manicured golf fairways.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Will the kids have access to extracurricular activities?</h3>
